snippet: President Obama’s top foreign policy aides said they planned to press Hassan Rowhani, Iran’s president-elect, to resume negotiations over his country’s nuclear program.
abstract: Pres Obama's top foreign policy aides say they plan to press Hassan Rouhani, Iran's newly elected president, to resume negotiations over his country's nuclear program.
lead_paragraph: President Obama’s top foreign policy aides said they planned to press Hassan Rowhani, Iran’s president-elect, to resume negotiations over his country’s nuclear program.

headline.main: U.S. Seems Eager for Nuclear Talks With Iran’s New Leader
headline.print_headline: U.S. Officials Appear Eager to Press New Iranian Leader for Nuclear Talks
